description:
In lichen_peer_remove() at lines 795-802:
```c
/* SECURITY: Zero pubkey before marking inactive */
secure_zero(entry->pubkey, sizeof(entry->pubkey));
secure_zero(entry->eui64, sizeof(entry->eui64));
entry->active = false;
LOG_INF("lichen_l2: peer removed ..%02x:%02x",
        eui64[6], eui64[7]);
```

The LOG_INF at line 799-800 logs eui64[6] and eui64[7], where eui64 is the FUNCTION PARAMETER (const uint8_t eui64[8] at line 735).

entry->eui64 was zeroed at line 797, but the function parameter eui64 still contains the original search key. The log output is CORRECT.

Re-examining line 799: it says eui64[6], not entry->eui64[6]. These are different variables:
- eui64: function parameter (the key we searched for)
- entry->eui64: peer_table entry's address field (now zeroed)

NO BUG - the code correctly logs the parameter, not the zeroed entry.
